commit.message: Treat BSD as Linux for libMAC detectation
Add platform define when enabling mac

Remove now unnecessary glib include in mac decoder

Pointed out by Daniel Pielmeier.

Fix the Monkey's Audio decoder to work with current Monkey's Audio (Fixes #33)

Using g_utf8_to_utf16 doesn't work because current Monkey's Audio
expects a different endianness of the multibyte character string.
Using GetUTF16FromANSI works for compiling only if namedspaced
correctly, and if namespaced correctly, it cannot link. Use a
similar approach for building the correct multibyte string.

Remove the DLLEXPORT define, to avoid a warning when including
the MAC headers.

Tested using the Monkey's Audio 10.20 SDK.
Add support for recent versions of Monkey's Audio

Add more supported formats to FFmpeg decoder 

Add a bunch of support formats to FFmpeg decoder to reduce amount of dependencies

commit.message: Bump version to 1.2
Update translations
Swtich CDDB port 888 to port 8880 in translations
Ignore *.poe files in the po directory

Fix compilation on ffmpeg 4

ffmpeg 5 apparently uses major version 59, not 58.

DRY up the preprocessor conditions while here, and change the
elif to else.

Reduce MAX_AUDIO_FRAME_SIZE in lavc decoder

Prevents crashing with MAP_STACK on OpenBSD due to a way too
large thread stack.
Allow compiling with ffmpeg 6 (and hopefully ffmpeg 5)
dec_lavc: garbage collect support for ancient FFmpeg API
Update it.po

Avoid double free of fi->trash.

info_window_close was freeing fi->trash (and not NULLing out the
pointer), then calling fi_delete which will free it again.

Avoid double free of send_button and add_tag_table.

These two widgets are created dynamically, but they're added to the info
window's widget structure so they will be destroyed automatically by GTK
when the window is destroyed.

Since the window close callback also calls fi_unload, this resulted in
the widgets being destroyed twice. NULL out the pointers in the callback
to prevent this.

Correct sendto length in send_message.

This function takes a message buffer and a length. Previously it was
sending length + 1 bytes, which isn't correct -- in several places it's
called with the buffer being a single char, and the matching code in
receive_message adds a \0 to the end of what it's received anyway.

Remove the use of recursive make for decoder/encoder/img directories

It doesn't seem like the use of recursive make is needed here,
and avoiding recursive make could result in faster compiles when
using parallel make.

Move mpeg decoder above sndfile decoder

Fixes display breakage for mpeg files when using sndfile 1.1.0,
which added mpeg encode/decode support.
Fix error creating config dirs

Don't call a variable "bool".

If one of the headers happens to #include <stdbool.h>, this'll clash
with the C99 type definition.
Document that podcast support is only for http and not https (Fixes #21)

Fix arr_strlcpy call in ifp_device.

directory_chooser needs to know the length of the target.
Fix corruption in aqualung.1
Update po files
Make SIGSEGV handler mention GitHub instead of SourceForge
Documentation updates

Update Changelog for 1.1 release

This also includes 1.0 release notes, since Changelog hadn't been
updated since 1.0-rc1.

Do not create version.h automatically, commit it to the repository

There is some value in having a development version display the
version string, but I think the benefits of keeping things simpler
outweigh that.

This defines the version as 1.1, since it will be released shortly.
